columns.description: Name of app for booking a trip

columns.name: 24 HOURS
columns.description: Base provides 24-hour service

columns.name: 2015 HONOR ROLL DRIVERS
columns.description: Number of drivers affiliated to the business who were members of the 2015 TLC Safety Honor Roll at the time of the ceremony in September 2015.

columns.name: 2015 HONOR ROLL BASE
columns.description: This business is a member of the 2015 TLC Safety Honor Roll.

columns.name: HOSTED VISION ZERO TRAINING
columns.description: This business has hosted TLC staff for a meeting to discuss Vision Zero and safe driving tips with drivers.

columns.name: VEHICLE SAFETY TECHNOLOGY USED
columns.description: Vehicles affiliated with this base have some form of vehicle safety technology, such as black boxes, cameras, or driver alert systems. This list includes both official TLC Vehicle Safety Technology Pilot participant vehicles as well as self-reported use of this kind of technology.

columns.name: BASE PROVIDES SAFETY TRAINING
columns.description: Businesses were invited to share if they provide other safety training programs beyond TLC and City requirements. (Self-reported)

columns.name: FATAL CRASHES
columns.description: All collisions involving a TLC-licensed vehicle affiliated with the base at the time of the crash resulting in a fatality (on-duty and off-duty).

columns.name: FATAL CRASH DETAILS
columns.description: TLC action in response to fatal crash, if applicable.

top.item: (Not found at fault. No TLC action)
(1 found at fault. TLC action: driver suspended)

columns.name: INJURY CRASHES PER VEHICLE
columns.description: All collisions involving a TLC-licensed vehicle affiliated with the base at the time of the crash resulting in an injury of any severity (major and minor injuries on-duty and off-duty irrespective of fault). This metric is per-vehicle, determined by the affiliated vehicle number for this base.

columns.name: SECTOR AVERAGE - INJURY CRASHES PER VEHICLE
columns.description: Average within the industry sector this base belongs to (livery, black car, or luxury limo)

columns.name: VEHICLE SAFETY VIOLATIONS PER VEHICLE
columns.description: A count of summonses naming vehicles affiliated to a base at the time the violation was issued and where the violator plead or was found guilty. Violations included in this metric fall into three categories: unlicensed activity, insurance requirements, and vehicle condition. This metric is per-vehicle, determined by the affiliated vehicle number for this base.

columns.name: SECTOR AVERAGE - VEHICLE SAFETY VIOLATIONS PER VEHICLE
columns.description: Average within the industry sector this base belongs to (livery, black car, or luxury limo)

columns.name: BASE SAFETY VIOLATIONS PER VEHICLE
columns.description: A count of summonses sent to bases, where the violating base plead or was found guilty. Violations included in this metric fall into four categories: accountability (e.g., trip data submission), accessibility, unlicensed activity, and vehicle condition. This metric is per-vehicle, determined by the affiliated vehicle number for this base.

columns.name: SECTOR AVERAGE -BASE SAFETY VIOLATIONS PER VEHICLE
columns.description: Average within the industry sector this base belongs to (livery, black car, or luxury limo)

columns.name: AFFILIATED VEHICLES
columns.description: Average number of vehicles affiliated with the base during the report period. This number is used for all per-vehicle calculations in the report.

columns.name: AVERAGE VEHICLE AGE
columns.description: An average of the age (in years) of all affiliated vehicles during the report period, determined through TLC vehicle licensing information.

columns.name: SECTOR AVERAGE - AVERAGE VEHICLE AGE
columns.description: Average within the industry sector this base belongs to (livery, black car, or luxury limo)

columns.name: PERCENT HYBRID & ALT-FUEL VEHICLES
columns.description: Percentage of vehicles affiliated to a base that have hybrid or electric engines or are models TLC has been alerted to that use alternative fuel.

columns.name: PERCENT WHEELCHAIR ACCESSIBLE VEHICLES
columns.description: Percentage of Boro Taxis affiliated to a base that is wheelchair-accessible.

columns.name: TOP VEHICLE MODELS - 1
columns.description: Most common make and model among base's affiliated vehicles

columns.name: TOP VEHICLE MODELS - 2
columns.description: Second-most common make and model among base's affiliated vehicles

columns.description: Fifth-most common make and model among base's affiliated vehicles

view.description: The Vision Zero Base Reports are collections of facts and statistics about individual TLC-regulated for-hire vehicle (FHV) businesses produced to help passengers identify businesses with the best safety records and support the for-hire industry’s efforts to achieve the highest levels of safety and service. Find definitions for the metrics used and more information on the reports here - http://www.nyc.gov/html/tlc/html/industry/vision_zero_base_reports.shtml
